{
  "texts": [
    "Control was in the hands of the owners of the machines.",
    "As a consequence, the privileged interests of media moguls tended to dominate the content they produced.",
    "These became \"mass media\" that \"manufactured consent\" (Herman andChomsky 1988 [2002]).",
    "They also disseminated \"propaganda\" (Bernays 1928(Bernays [2005]]) to maintain their class interests in the existing social order.",
    "The owners of the means of production of meaning shaped the content of meaning, while the masses were left few options but to consume and conform."
  ]
}